communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

For the period of 01/01/2022 until date of processing:

1. Any digital communications (including but not limited to emails, text messages, instant messages, and recorded phone or video calls or metadata) as well as documents, (including but not limited to PDF, word processing, excel, and slide documents) to or from the accounts for Sheriff Corpus and Chief of Staff/Assistant Sheriff Aenlle.

2. Any digital communications (including but not limited to emails, text messages, instant messages, and recorded phone or video calls or metadata) as well as documents, (including but not limited to PDF, word processing, excel, and slide documents) that mention "Corpus", "Aenlle", "Cordell", "Tapia", "Monaghan", "Hsiung" or their associated usernames on internal systems.

Please include all attachments with all messages.

In all cases, I expect there could be personnel- and case- related messages that cannot be disclosed. Please exclude those. I am only interested in any communications not tied to particular cases and not explicitly covered by exemptions regarding personnel.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ewen Cheslack-Postava

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Fellis traffic stop
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am looking to obtain the body cam footage and any potential squad car footage leading up to the stop. The stop occurred on 11-15-24 between the hours of 4 pm and 5pm. Infraction number 4A0762241

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Justin Fellis
